history.text: Hello, Have you seen the movie Zootopia?
I have and my kids love it, have you?
Yes, and I enjoyed the movie too. What was your favorite character?
Nick Wilde because of his tactics but in the end still was a good guy
I didn't think i would like the movie when i first heard about it though.  What were your initial thoughts?
I agree, but I also liked Judy Hopps, she was fun
The reviews sum it up pretty well and there were some subtle thought prevoking symbolisms in it.
I liked the whole idea of an animal "world" and I liked how the animators translated the whole concept.
like the nature vs nurture concept
I think the idea of a small bunny taking on a big case was a good idea and it showed some important lessons.
I especially liked how Judy got Nick to help by blackmailing him
That was fun and the crime boss Mr. Big was hilarious
The irony of mr. big being a tiny rat/mouse was pretty comical
the unrealistic expectation of 10 hours being left to solve the case really put the pressure on judy and nick
I thought it was also kind of Nick to defend Judy when Chief Bogo wanted to fire her
yeah with no leads he still had faith in her
And the back story of Nick was touching, you got to understand how he became a con man
Lionheart hiding the savages in the asylum while trying to solve the cause really made him look guilty
I don't understand though, how Judy could upset Nick at the press conference after all they went through

Yeah it shows how people don't understand what they are saying and how hurtful it can be.  Really makes you think about what we say on a daily basis that could be considered hateful, racist, rude, etc.
Bellwether becoming the mayor wasn't expected since she was so quiet.
True and it showed because Judy felt guilty and ended up quitting her job
If more people realized the affects of their words, we might live in a better place instead of just denying that it't harmful.
and Bellwether being mayor did come out of no where. I didn't see that coming
The switch from the obvious nighthowlers being wolves to flowers wasn't expected either.

Right, who would have ever thought that a flower would cause animals to go "
savage"
Using the recording to catch Bellwether was a fun move since that's how Judy got nick to help
Yeah, looks like Judy taught Nick something.
ironic too that the their was a weasel
thief
If i hadn't already seen the movie i would probably want to after reading the summary
Overall, I think that the movie was fun and had some lessons taught
exactly and kid friendly...also one you can watch more than once
